Class AbstractContinuousDomainDataset

  • java.lang.Object

    public abstract class AbstractContinuousDomainDataset
extends AbstractDataset
    Partial implementation of a Dataset with a continuous domain which performs spatial indexing of features.
    Author:
    Guy Griffiths

      • extractProfileFeatures

        public List<? extends ProfileFeature> extractProfileFeatures(Set<String> varIds,
                                                             PlottingDomainParams params)
                                                      throws DataReadingException
        Description copied from interface: Dataset
        Extracts ProfileFeature(s) from the Dataset
        Parameters:
        varIds - The variable IDs to extract. If this is null then all variable IDs will be plotted. Any non-scalar parent variables will have all of their child variables extracted.
        params - The PlottingDomainParams describing the domain to be extracted:
        • PlottingDomainParams.getTargetZ() is ignored.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getZExtent() is non- null, all ProfileFeatures whose domains have any intersection with this vertical extent will be extracted. The domains of the extracted ProfileFeature s will be the entire available domains, not just the intersection.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getZExtent() is null, no constraint will be placed on the vertical domain of the ProfileFeatures to extract.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getTExtent() is non- null, all measurements which fall entirely within the extent given by PlottingDomainParams.getTExtent() will be extracted
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getTExtent() is null only profiles matching the time specified by PlottingDomainParams.getTargetT() will be extracted. In the case of a gridded dataset a time is considered to match if the method TimeAxis#contains(org.joda.time.DateTime) on its time axis returns true for the target time. For a non-gridded dataset, the feature time must exactly match the target time.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getTargetT() and PlottingDomainParams.getTExtent() are both null, ProfileFeatures for all available time values will be extracted.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getBbox() is non- null, all measurements falling within PlottingDomainParams.getBbox() will be returned.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getBbox() is null, only measurements which match the horizontal position given by PlottingDomainParams.getTargetHorizontalPosition() will be extracted. In the case of a gridded feature, this will be the profile of the grid cell which the position falls into, but for a dataset with a continuous HorizontalDomain only exact matches will be extracted
        • If both PlottingDomainParams.getTargetHorizontalPosition() and PlottingDomainParams.getBbox() are null no constraint is placed on horizontal positions - e.g. for a gridded field a profile will be returned for every horizontal grid point.
        • If a PlottingDomainParams.getTargetHorizontalPosition() is non-null, the resulting Collection will be sorted according to distance (in co-ordinate units) from the target position
        Returns:
        A Collection of ProfileFeatures, sorted by their distance from the target horizontal position, if it exists.
        Throws:
        DataReadingException - if there is a problem reading the underlying data

      • extractTimeseriesFeatures

        public List<? extends PointSeriesFeature> extractTimeseriesFeatures(Set<String> varIds,
                                                                    PlottingDomainParams params)
                                                             throws DataReadingException
        Description copied from interface: Dataset
        Extracts PointSeriesFeature(s) from the Dataset
        Parameters:
        varIds - The variable IDs to extract. If this is null then all variable IDs will be plotted. Any non-scalar parent variables will have all of their child variables extracted.
        params - The PlottingDomainParams describing the domain to be extracted:
        • PlottingDomainParams.getTargetT() is ignored.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getTExtent() is non- null, all PointSeriesFeatures whose domains have any intersection with this vertical extent will be extracted. The domains of the extracted PointSeriesFeatures will be the entire available domains, not just the intersection.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getTExtent() is null, no constraint will be placed on the temporal domain of the PointSeriesFeatures to extract
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getZExtent() is non- null , all measurements which fall entirely within the extent given by PlottingDomainParams.getZExtent() will be extracted
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getZExtent() is null only profiles matching the depth specified by PlottingDomainParams.getTargetZ() will be extracted. In the case of a gridded dataset a depth is considered to match if the method VerticalAxis#contains(Double) on its vertical axis returns true for the target depth. For a non-gridded dataset, the feature depth must exactly match the target depth.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getTargetZ() and PlottingDomainParams.getZExtent() are both null, PointSeriesFeatures for all available elevations will be extracted.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getBbox() is non- null, all measurements falling within PlottingDomainParams.getBbox() will be returned.
        • If PlottingDomainParams.getBbox() is null, only measurements which match the horizontal position given by PlottingDomainParams.getTargetHorizontalPosition() will be extracted. In the case of a gridded feature, this will be the timeseries of the grid cell which the position falls into, but for a dataset with a continuous HorizontalDomain only exact matches will be extracted
        • If both PlottingDomainParams.getTargetHorizontalPosition() and PlottingDomainParams.getBbox() are null no constraint is placed on horizontal positions - e.g. for a gridded field a timeseries will be returned for every horizontal grid point.
        • If a PlottingDomainParams.getTargetHorizontalPosition() is non-null, the resulting Collection will be sorted according to distance (in co-ordinate units) from the target position
        Returns:
        A Collection of PointSeriesFeatures, sorted by their distance from the target horizontal position, if it exists.
        Throws:
        DataReadingException - if there is a problem reading the underlying data
